            <p>Folk healers in the Himalayan region of Sikkim have used it as a tonic for "all illnesses", with claims that it improves appetite, stamina, libido, endurance, and sleeping patterns.</p>
            <p>Its contemporary use has gained popularity as an adaptogenic functional mushroom, particularly in regards to performance, as it stimulates the body's cells to produce more of the molecule adenosine triphosphate - which is essential for delivering energy to the muscles and improving your body's use of oxygen during exercise.</p>
